WEBVTT

00:01.790 --> 00:03.960
♪♪

00:03.960 --> 00:05.080
Hello?

00:05.080 --> 00:06.380
Jackie?
Yeah?

00:06.380 --> 00:08.620
Dawn from Cook County
Meat and Fish.

00:08.620 --> 00:10.460
Hi.
Oh, thank you for coming.

00:10.460 --> 00:12.080
You look exactly
like I pictured you

00:12.080 --> 00:13.750
from all of
our phone calls.

00:13.750 --> 00:16.040
You are, too. But weirdly,
you sound different.

00:17.380 --> 00:19.750
Oh, I love this space!

00:19.750 --> 00:21.210
[ Chuckles ]

00:21.210 --> 00:22.830
You know, a lot of new
restaurants try too hard.

00:22.830 --> 00:24.210
Yeah, not us.

00:24.210 --> 00:25.790
We know what it takes
to get the job done,

00:25.790 --> 00:27.380
and we do
just a little bit less.

00:27.380 --> 00:29.210
[ Both laugh ]

00:29.210 --> 00:30.920
You're hilarious,
you know that?

00:30.920 --> 00:31.960
No, I'm not. Am I?

00:31.960 --> 00:33.790
Yeah, heck yeah.

00:33.790 --> 00:35.920
Okay,
so, I got your menu.

00:35.920 --> 00:38.210
I will put together
a preliminary order.

00:38.210 --> 00:39.330
That way,
you can price me

00:39.330 --> 00:41.540
against other suppliers
you're considering.

00:41.540 --> 00:42.620
I mean, thieves.

00:42.620 --> 00:44.670
[ Laughing ]
No, I'm kidding.

00:44.670 --> 00:45.790
I mean suppliers.

00:45.790 --> 00:46.790
Who steal.

00:46.790 --> 00:48.580
[ Both laugh ]

00:48.580 --> 00:50.290
Sorry I'm late.

00:50.290 --> 00:52.330
D.J. came over
to watch the baby,

00:52.330 --> 00:54.750
and she hit him in the eye
with a rattle.

00:54.750 --> 00:56.920
He cried, she cried,
and then I cried

00:56.920 --> 00:58.620
'cause I don't have
better child care.

00:58.620 --> 01:02.250
Becky, this is Dawn
from Cook County Meat and Fish.

01:02.250 --> 01:03.960
She thinks I'm hilarious.

01:03.960 --> 01:05.250
Such a pleasure,
Becky.

01:05.250 --> 01:07.080
I have to tell you,
I think comfort food

01:07.080 --> 01:09.710
in this location
is gonna be a big winner.

01:09.710 --> 01:13.920
The only thing you're missing is
a signature, big-ticket item.

01:13.920 --> 01:14.960
Steak.

01:16.040 --> 01:18.120
You need to offer
a good steak.

01:18.120 --> 01:20.120
We can't afford
a good steak.

01:20.120 --> 01:21.580
And I'm not just talking
about the customers.

01:21.580 --> 01:23.460
I'm talking about the people
that own the restaurant.

01:23.460 --> 01:26.790
Becky, Dawn has
a fantastic background.

01:26.790 --> 01:28.960
She was a buyer
for a big restaurant chain.

01:28.960 --> 01:31.170
I started this company
after the managing partner

01:31.170 --> 01:32.790
at the old place
groped me in the stock room.

01:32.790 --> 01:34.830
Can you believe that?

01:34.830 --> 01:37.670
Same thing.
The stock room.
Happened to me.
In the stock room.

01:37.670 --> 01:39.380
Yep,
and look at us now.

01:39.380 --> 01:41.460
Well, I'm looking at you
in those boots,

01:41.460 --> 01:43.670
and I got to tell you,
I love those.

01:43.670 --> 01:46.880
Oh, well, they'd look good
on your cute, little figure.

01:46.880 --> 01:50.460
Oh, no, I could never
pull off boots like that.

01:50.460 --> 01:51.620
Oh,
you wouldn't have to.

01:51.620 --> 01:53.170
Your boyfriend
would be pulling them off.

01:53.170 --> 01:55.380
And he wouldn't stop there!
[ Chuckles ]

01:55.380 --> 01:58.580
Oh, yeah, you better
quit it right now!

01:58.580 --> 02:01.210
I mean, I --

02:01.210 --> 02:02.880
I don't even have
a boyfriend.

02:02.880 --> 02:04.380
Oh. Neither do I.

02:04.380 --> 02:05.750
But so what?

02:05.750 --> 02:07.670
Here's to being
our own soul mates.

02:07.670 --> 02:09.620
Amen!
Amen.

02:09.620 --> 02:11.620
Yes, we love ourselves,
and men don't want us.

02:11.620 --> 02:13.210
Can we get back
to the food?

02:14.540 --> 02:15.500
Let's talk prices.

02:15.500 --> 02:16.620
Okay.

02:16.620 --> 02:18.120
Well, this has been fun.

02:18.120 --> 02:20.250
I will make a list
of what I think you need,

02:20.250 --> 02:22.040
and I will send you
an itemized estimate.

02:25.250 --> 02:26.830
Au revoir.

02:28.830 --> 02:30.580
That's French
for "goodbye."

02:32.290 --> 02:33.670
I know.

02:33.670 --> 02:35.710
Everybody knows.

02:35.710 --> 02:37.670
And before you fall in love
with her,

02:37.670 --> 02:39.620
we should discuss
whether we can afford her.

02:39.620 --> 02:43.000
I love her.
I'm not in love with her.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.040
[ Grunting ]

02:45.040 --> 02:46.580
Oh, my God!
What happened?

02:46.580 --> 02:48.790
He tweaked his back
nailing the floorboard.

02:48.790 --> 02:51.790
I'm fine. I just got to soak it
and then lay down.

02:51.790 --> 02:53.170
No, you need
to see a doctor.

02:53.170 --> 02:54.210
I'm gonna take you
to urgent care.

02:54.210 --> 02:56.290
It's just a twinge.
I'm fine.

02:56.290 --> 02:57.620
Ow!

02:57.620 --> 02:59.000
♪ I feel good ♪

03:00.710 --> 03:03.290
♪ I knew that I would ♪

03:03.290 --> 03:04.920
Whoa!

03:04.920 --> 03:07.620
♪ I feel nice ♪

03:07.620 --> 03:09.210
♪ Like sugar and spice ♪

03:09.210 --> 03:11.880
Jackie: Ohh, Dan.

03:14.620 --> 03:22.580
♪♪

03:22.580 --> 03:30.540
♪♪

03:30.540 --> 03:38.540
♪♪

03:38.540 --> 03:46.500
♪♪

03:49.540 --> 03:51.710
"The Conners" is
recorded in front of
a live studio audience.

03:51.710 --> 03:54.120
[ Groaning ]

03:56.380 --> 03:58.420
[ Groaning continues ]

03:58.420 --> 04:00.120
Can I help you
with something?

04:00.120 --> 04:02.120
If I need help,
I'll ask for it.

04:04.290 --> 04:05.920
See?

04:08.620 --> 04:10.670
Easy peasy.

04:10.670 --> 04:12.210
Huh.

04:12.210 --> 04:14.710
Harris got a letter
from Central Illinois State.

04:14.710 --> 04:16.120
The college
or the penitentiary?

04:19.880 --> 04:21.620
"Congratulations.
You're a Mud Turtle."

04:21.620 --> 04:23.080
Oh, my God, she got in!

04:23.080 --> 04:24.790
That's great!

04:24.790 --> 04:26.790
Finally, someone from
this family made it to college.

04:26.790 --> 04:28.000
Hey, I went to college.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.670
You went to art school.

04:31.500 --> 04:34.120
That's basically Color Me Mine
with a library.

04:36.040 --> 04:38.790
How much is this college
gonna cost you?

04:38.790 --> 04:40.250
I don't know,

04:40.250 --> 04:42.250
but now that I'm a divorced,
unemployed single mom,

04:42.250 --> 04:44.380
we might actually have a shot
at some financial aid.

04:44.380 --> 04:47.170
My plan to destroy my life
is working.

04:47.170 --> 04:49.830
I told you
to stick with it.

04:49.830 --> 04:51.210
You know what --
Harris asked me

04:51.210 --> 04:52.830
to bring some clothes
over to Odessa's.

04:52.830 --> 04:54.710
I'm gonna take them over there
right now and show this to her.

04:54.710 --> 04:56.920
Ah, she's finally gonna let you
into the dope den.

04:56.920 --> 04:59.000
Ah, at least now I got a shot
at getting her out of there

04:59.000 --> 05:01.170
and into a dorm room!

05:01.170 --> 05:02.880
No drugs there.

05:09.750 --> 05:10.960
Hello, Odessa.

05:10.960 --> 05:12.500
Harris is expecting me.

05:12.500 --> 05:14.830
[ British accent ]
Before the other side you see,

05:14.830 --> 05:17.460
answer me
these questions three.

05:19.080 --> 05:21.170
Uh, somebody
just smoked a bowl

05:21.170 --> 05:23.710
watching
"Monty Python's Holy Grail."

05:23.710 --> 05:25.290
Correct.
You may pass.

05:25.290 --> 05:28.120
[ Vacuum cleaner whirring ]

05:28.120 --> 05:30.170
[ Normal voice ]
Not what you expected, huh?

05:30.170 --> 05:33.170
We do the human sacrifices
in my bedroom.

05:35.620 --> 05:37.500
Hey, Mom.

05:37.500 --> 05:38.790
Guess what.

05:38.790 --> 05:41.040
You are a Mud Turtle.

05:41.040 --> 05:43.880
[ Whirring stops ]
I haven't put on makeup yet.
Give me a break.

05:43.880 --> 05:46.290
No.
You got into college.

05:46.290 --> 05:47.790
Central Illinois State.

05:47.790 --> 05:49.120
We've got a tour
on Friday.

05:49.120 --> 05:52.290
Yeah,
I'm not going to that.

05:52.290 --> 05:53.790
What? Why not?

05:53.790 --> 05:56.170
I start working at
Price Warehouse next Monday.

05:56.170 --> 05:57.880
They've got a program
for employees

05:57.880 --> 05:59.670
to get a business degree
online.

05:59.670 --> 06:02.210
Well, I-I don't want you
to go to school online.

06:02.210 --> 06:05.420
It's a great deal, Mom.
It's only 350 bucks a year.

06:05.420 --> 06:07.250
Yeah, but I want you
to live in a dorm

06:07.250 --> 06:10.210
and gain 15 pounds
and get mono.

06:10.210 --> 06:11.670
That's for rich kids.

06:11.670 --> 06:13.250
We don't have the money
for college.

06:13.250 --> 06:15.210
Yeah, no, we already
have an appointment

06:15.210 --> 06:16.670
with the financial aid
office.

06:16.670 --> 06:18.170
They want to help us.

06:18.170 --> 06:20.580
A-And see? They look forward
to meeting you.

06:20.580 --> 06:22.710
Nobody ever looks forward
to meeting you.

06:22.710 --> 06:25.120
[ Scoffs ]
They write that to everyone.

06:25.120 --> 06:28.170
No, they don't. This is
written directly to you,
"Mr. Harris Coner."

06:28.170 --> 06:30.420
[ Scoffs ]

06:30.420 --> 06:32.960
And why do you want
a business degree, anyway?

06:32.960 --> 06:34.420
You should study writing.

06:34.420 --> 06:35.790
You remember
when the Sun-Times printed

06:35.790 --> 06:38.580
your "I Hate Lanford" article
and everybody was so angry?

06:38.580 --> 06:40.790
That's the happiest
I've ever seen you.

06:40.790 --> 06:42.670
Yeah.

06:42.670 --> 06:45.210
The Mayor called me an
embarrassment to the community.

06:45.210 --> 06:47.080
Of course
that made me feel good.

06:49.040 --> 06:50.210
Okay.

06:50.210 --> 06:51.960
I'll go on the tour.
For you.

06:51.960 --> 06:54.920
Mud Turtles!

06:54.920 --> 06:57.040
A mud turtle
is the worst mascot ever.

06:57.040 --> 06:58.170
What's the cheer?

06:58.170 --> 07:00.830
"Go, fight.
Do something."

07:03.580 --> 07:06.080
Mud Turtles! Whoo!

07:08.960 --> 07:10.620
Whew!

07:10.620 --> 07:14.120
Instead of an estimate, we got
a bill from your gal pal, Dawn,

07:14.120 --> 07:16.920
which is weird, because
I don't remember hiring her.

07:16.920 --> 07:18.880
She made a good case
for her company at lunch,

07:18.880 --> 07:20.460
so I went for it.

07:20.460 --> 07:23.330
So now decisions are being made
without me over lunch?

07:23.330 --> 07:27.420
Well, we were hungry after
our Pinot and Painting class.

07:27.420 --> 07:29.790
I'm learning so much
about myself.

07:29.790 --> 07:32.920
I always knew I could drink,
but I didn't know I could paint.

07:32.920 --> 07:35.880
This is twice
what we agreed we could afford.

07:35.880 --> 07:38.120
Look at what she's charging us
for vegetables.

07:38.120 --> 07:39.540
They're all
locally sourced.

07:39.540 --> 07:41.120
I don't care
if they're locally sourced.

07:41.120 --> 07:44.170
I care
if they're locally eaten.

07:44.170 --> 07:46.170
And she went ahead
and put the steak on here.

07:46.170 --> 07:48.500
Dawn showed me
that with an upgraded menu,

07:48.500 --> 07:50.750
we can pull people
as far away as Chicago.

07:50.750 --> 07:52.500
You're right.

07:52.500 --> 07:55.750
You can't get a good steak
in Chicago!

07:55.750 --> 07:58.790
You got to drive an hour to
a roadside diner in a dying town

07:58.790 --> 08:00.460
that bought their steak
from Chicago.

08:00.460 --> 08:04.040
I'm sorry that you don't
trust Dawn, but I do.

08:05.000 --> 08:07.420
Jackie, okay, um...

08:07.420 --> 08:11.380
I might be wrong,
but Dawn is a saleswoman.

08:11.380 --> 08:13.790
Isn't it possible that she's
pretending to be your friend

08:13.790 --> 08:16.040
to ratchet up the bill?

08:16.040 --> 08:17.920
I'm afraid she might be
taking advantage of you.

08:17.920 --> 08:20.040
Au contraire.

08:20.040 --> 08:21.540
I'm taking advantage of her

08:21.540 --> 08:23.960
by being her friend
and picking her brain.

08:23.960 --> 08:25.830
"Au contraire"?

08:25.830 --> 08:28.750
Now you're talking
like her.

08:28.750 --> 08:30.790
You've never said "au contraire"
in your life!

08:30.790 --> 08:34.250
Au contraire!
I said it just a second ago!

08:34.250 --> 08:35.500
Dawn likes me.

08:35.500 --> 08:37.790
She invited me
to the Rockford Wine Festival.

08:37.790 --> 08:39.120
Well, okay.

08:39.120 --> 08:40.920
If she's really
your friend,

08:40.920 --> 08:42.790
maybe you should
cut the order in half

08:42.790 --> 08:45.540
and see if she still wants to go
to the wine festival with you.

08:45.540 --> 08:48.170
Oh, she'll still want me to go.
It's a fait accompli.

08:49.620 --> 08:54.960
♪♪

08:54.960 --> 08:57.710
Okay. Your counselor
will be right in.

08:57.710 --> 08:58.920
See you around campus,
Harris.

08:58.920 --> 08:59.920
[ Chuckles ]

08:59.920 --> 09:01.710
Hm? He's cute.

09:01.710 --> 09:03.750
Why would I date him
when there's professors here?

09:05.710 --> 09:07.420
Hi. I'm Helen.

09:07.420 --> 09:09.170
I'm here to help
with your financial aid.

09:09.170 --> 09:10.330
Hi.

09:10.330 --> 09:12.540
So, Harris, what did you think
of the campus?

09:12.540 --> 09:14.250
It was cool.

09:14.250 --> 09:16.790
I like that the student paper
investigates real stuff.

09:16.790 --> 09:18.330
And it's far away enough
from my house

09:18.330 --> 09:20.460
that my mom can't visit
on a whim.

09:20.460 --> 09:21.580
[ Chuckles ]

09:21.580 --> 09:23.250
Well, Harris, we thought
your admissions packet

09:23.250 --> 09:24.710
was really special.

09:24.710 --> 09:27.830
Your "I Hate Lanford" essay
was spot-on.

09:27.830 --> 09:30.210
My ex is from there.

09:30.210 --> 09:32.330
Thanks.
I'm glad you liked it.

09:32.330 --> 09:34.880
Uh, along with showing you
that Harris is special,

09:34.880 --> 09:37.920
our application should've also
shown you that we're super poor.

09:37.920 --> 09:39.500
Like Dust Bowl poor.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.920
That's why we put together
a comprehensive aid package

09:42.920 --> 09:44.420
to make this happen.

09:44.420 --> 09:45.670
Sweet.

09:45.670 --> 09:46.750
Okay.

09:46.750 --> 09:47.750
Loan...

09:47.750 --> 09:49.960
loan...

09:49.960 --> 09:51.080
loan.

09:51.080 --> 09:52.420
Um...
[ Chuckles ]

09:52.420 --> 09:54.040
Where are all the grants
and scholarships --

09:54.040 --> 09:55.960
you know,
the free money?

09:55.960 --> 09:57.460
Well, I'm sure
you folks expected

09:57.460 --> 09:59.170
that you'd be
contributing something.

09:59.170 --> 10:01.080
Uh, yeah, something,

10:01.080 --> 10:03.670
but you have us paying
everything, and with interest.

10:03.670 --> 10:05.250
I mean,
we can't afford this.

10:05.250 --> 10:06.460
According to this chart,

10:06.460 --> 10:08.710
it'll take me 20 years
to pay back these loans.

10:08.710 --> 10:12.290
20 years goes by
faster than you think.

10:12.290 --> 10:14.750
You can waste that on a man
everybody said was wrong for you

10:14.750 --> 10:15.710
but you knew better.

10:15.710 --> 10:17.210
[ Chuckles ]

10:20.290 --> 10:21.670
I'm confused.

10:21.670 --> 10:24.540
I mean, the letter you sent us
promised to help us.

10:24.540 --> 10:26.170
I want to.

10:26.170 --> 10:27.960
Um, does Harris have
a unique skill

10:27.960 --> 10:30.540
that might qualify her
for a scholarship?

10:30.540 --> 10:34.790
A female tuba player is
a college admissions home run.

10:34.790 --> 10:35.960
Do you play the tuba?

10:35.960 --> 10:37.170
Yes.
No.

10:38.750 --> 10:41.000
This is a waste of time.
I shouldn't have come here.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.540
No, Harris, wait.
We're still talking.

10:42.540 --> 10:44.330
I'm done.

10:44.330 --> 10:46.460
I felt good about my plan,
and then I let you drag me here

10:46.460 --> 10:48.120
and show me everything
that I can't have.

10:48.120 --> 10:49.170
Thanks a lot.

10:50.380 --> 10:52.540
You know what?
This whole thing is a scam.

10:52.540 --> 10:54.710
You just bring people down here,
get their hopes up,

10:54.710 --> 10:56.670
and then try to trick them
into crippling loans

10:56.670 --> 10:59.170
they'll be paying back
for the rest of their lives.

10:59.170 --> 11:01.540
You should be ashamed
of yourself.

11:01.540 --> 11:04.500
You know, I want
my $100 application fee back.

11:04.500 --> 11:07.380
I'm sorry.
We -- We can't do that.

11:07.380 --> 11:08.830
Well, that check was
never gonna clear anyway.

11:08.830 --> 11:09.830
Good day.

11:09.830 --> 11:13.330
♪♪

11:13.330 --> 11:15.330
Dan?

11:15.330 --> 11:17.040
Yeah?

11:17.040 --> 11:19.380
Uh, I heard
you hurt your back,

11:19.380 --> 11:22.580
so I came by
to check on you.

11:22.580 --> 11:24.290
Mark said you've been in there
for a couple hours.

11:24.290 --> 11:25.460
You okay?

11:25.460 --> 11:27.380
I can't pull myself
out of the tub.

11:27.380 --> 11:28.830
[ Sighs ]

11:28.830 --> 11:31.330
You're gonna get sick
if you stay in there too long.

11:32.670 --> 11:33.790
I'm coming in.

11:33.790 --> 11:35.250
Aw, geez!

11:35.250 --> 11:39.210
Uh...okay, give me a second
to cover up, would ya?

11:41.290 --> 11:42.330
Alright.

11:44.790 --> 11:45.790
[ Sighs ]

11:47.040 --> 11:49.460
Oh, rainbow bubbles?
[ Chuckles ]

11:49.460 --> 11:51.830
I didn't picture you
as a bath bomb kind of guy.

11:51.830 --> 11:53.960
I'm a very complex man.

11:55.330 --> 11:58.380
I have a gay grandson
who gave me this for Christmas.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.750
I thought
the Epsom salts would help.

12:00.750 --> 12:02.670
I didn't know
the glitter and the color

12:02.670 --> 12:04.210
would turn me
into a merman.

12:05.830 --> 12:08.620
Uh, your -- your hair
has shampoo in it.

12:08.620 --> 12:10.960
Yeah, I-I was gonna rinse it off
with the hose attachment.

12:10.960 --> 12:12.620
It fell in the tub.

12:12.620 --> 12:16.670
Well, I could...
reach in there and root around.

12:16.670 --> 12:18.460
Might change our relationship.
[ Chuckles ]

12:20.000 --> 12:22.250
Oh, it's -- it's just
a little shampoo.

12:22.250 --> 12:24.210
I'll get it.

12:24.210 --> 12:25.500
Um, here.

12:25.500 --> 12:26.580
[ Grunts ]

12:26.580 --> 12:27.960
Okay.

12:27.960 --> 12:29.120
Okay.

12:31.000 --> 12:32.000
There.

12:34.460 --> 12:37.210
See?
That's not so bad, is it?

12:37.210 --> 12:38.540
It's kind of nice.

12:38.540 --> 12:39.750
Oh, soap in my eye.
Soap in my eye!

12:39.750 --> 12:40.920
Oh. Here, I got it.

12:43.460 --> 12:44.670
Okay.

12:46.420 --> 12:47.920
Yeah.

12:54.380 --> 12:55.250
Um...

12:56.710 --> 12:58.380
Alright.

12:58.380 --> 13:00.710
Let's get you
out of that tub.

13:00.710 --> 13:03.250
Now, do you want to, uh,
have some more towels,

13:03.250 --> 13:04.670
or should I
just close my eyes?

13:04.670 --> 13:07.290
More towels. You're gonna peek.
You can't help yourself.

13:09.830 --> 13:12.500
[ Both laughing ]

13:12.500 --> 13:14.170
Well,
it looks like you two

13:14.170 --> 13:15.830
had a good time
at the wine festival.

13:15.830 --> 13:17.790
I only had one glass.

13:17.790 --> 13:20.540
I don't know why I threw up
in the Uber, but...

13:20.540 --> 13:22.210
[ Laughs ]

13:22.210 --> 13:24.080
Dawn bought me this.

13:24.080 --> 13:26.000
Ohh.
I'll be right back.

13:29.830 --> 13:32.920
Well,
guess I was wrong.

13:32.920 --> 13:35.210
She really is
your friend.

13:35.210 --> 13:36.460
She still took you
to the festival

13:36.460 --> 13:37.710
even though
you cut the order.

13:37.710 --> 13:39.380
Well...

13:39.380 --> 13:40.880
You did cut the order?

13:40.880 --> 13:41.790
Eh...not exactly.

13:41.790 --> 13:43.040
Jackie!

13:43.040 --> 13:45.040
Oh, I don't want to know,
Becky.

13:45.040 --> 13:46.540
Dawn's the only friend
I've got.

13:46.540 --> 13:47.830
That's not true.

13:47.830 --> 13:49.000
Women don't like me,
Becky!

13:56.420 --> 13:59.420
I'm a woman,
and I used to like you.

13:59.420 --> 14:02.290
I'm 64, and I'm tired
of being lonely.

14:02.290 --> 14:03.830
She's the first friend
I've had in years,

14:03.830 --> 14:05.500
and I don't want
to lose her.

14:05.500 --> 14:08.330
But isn't it better to find out
now if she's playing you,

14:08.330 --> 14:10.670
before you get
any more attached to her?

14:10.670 --> 14:12.170
Or I never find out

14:12.170 --> 14:14.250
and I live
in a happy fantasy world

14:14.250 --> 14:17.580
where I go from wine festival
to wine festival.

14:18.880 --> 14:20.960
Look, I just don't want
to see you get lied to

14:20.960 --> 14:23.290
in another relationship.

14:23.290 --> 14:24.920
You deserve a real friend.

14:24.920 --> 14:26.880
I know I do.

14:26.880 --> 14:29.210
How about a glass of wine
for courage?

14:30.540 --> 14:32.710
But just one.
I don't want to get sloppy.

14:32.710 --> 14:34.710
♪♪

14:40.210 --> 14:42.790
What are you doing
out here?

14:42.790 --> 14:44.580
Trying to freeze myself
to death

14:44.580 --> 14:47.460
so Harris can get
some hardship money for college.

14:47.460 --> 14:49.040
You might want
to take your shoes off.

14:49.040 --> 14:50.460
It'll go faster.

14:54.290 --> 14:56.830
The school wouldn't
give us any money.

14:56.830 --> 14:58.500
If I'd saved anything,

14:58.500 --> 15:01.830
my daughter wouldn't be
giving up her dreams at 17.

15:01.830 --> 15:03.920
Hi. Welcome
to the Conner family.

15:03.920 --> 15:05.210
Pbhhhht!

15:07.170 --> 15:08.540
Dad,
you should've seen her face

15:08.540 --> 15:10.750
when she was
walking around that campus.

15:10.750 --> 15:13.420
I swear
she was actually smiling.

15:15.290 --> 15:17.000
I feel like I failed her.

15:17.000 --> 15:19.960
Don't beat yourself up.

15:19.960 --> 15:22.580
It sounds like she's got
a few things figured out.

15:22.580 --> 15:24.460
Hey, I'm sure
it's a great school,

15:24.460 --> 15:26.790
but she probably doesn't want
all that debt.

15:26.790 --> 15:30.170
And a business degree,
that's not a bad idea.

15:31.120 --> 15:32.920
I want more for her.

15:32.920 --> 15:35.540
I know what you want.

15:35.540 --> 15:38.080
But it's time to get on board
to the future she's building.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.250
And if you're not careful,
you're gonna make her feel like

15:42.250 --> 15:44.790
she's never accomplished
anything in your eyes.

15:44.790 --> 15:46.460
[ Chuckling ] Oh.
You mean like art school?

15:46.460 --> 15:47.250
[ Hisses ]

15:47.250 --> 15:48.580
[ Hisses ]

15:51.250 --> 15:54.000
You know where I'm gonna be
Monday morning?

15:54.000 --> 15:57.540
At Harris' first day of work,
congratulating her.

15:57.540 --> 15:59.120
And you should be, too.

16:00.420 --> 16:01.540
Wait.

16:01.540 --> 16:04.080
Is that glitter
in your eyebrows?

16:04.080 --> 16:06.080
I wish it was
just in my eyebrows.

16:12.330 --> 16:15.080
So, Dawn, um...

16:15.080 --> 16:17.500
I'm just gonna say this.

16:17.500 --> 16:19.080
I have to cut
our food order.

16:19.080 --> 16:20.500
I got
a little carried away,

16:20.500 --> 16:22.580
and I didn't discuss it
with Becky.

16:22.580 --> 16:24.250
Well,
that's disappointing.

16:24.250 --> 16:25.250
I know.

16:25.250 --> 16:26.580
And even though
it wasn't real,

16:26.580 --> 16:28.420
I really enjoyed
being your friend.

16:28.420 --> 16:30.040
What are you talking about?
What wasn't real?

16:30.040 --> 16:31.420
This. Us.

16:31.420 --> 16:32.670
I know you were
just being nice to me

16:32.670 --> 16:35.000
so I'd buy more stuff,
and I get it.

16:35.000 --> 16:37.290
I'm not hilarious.
I don't have a cute figure.

16:37.290 --> 16:40.210
I'm just a woman
with a roadside restaurant.

16:40.210 --> 16:43.250
So, you think I was just
pretending to be your friend

16:43.250 --> 16:45.540
so I could make a few bucks
on an order?

16:45.540 --> 16:47.170
That's ridiculous.

16:47.170 --> 16:49.330
Look, you're cool,
you're smart,

16:49.330 --> 16:51.500
you're just damaged enough
to be entertaining.

16:53.290 --> 16:55.080
And you set off
all those car alarms

16:55.080 --> 16:56.960
to shorten the line
at the wine festival.

16:59.080 --> 17:01.790
When you want wine,
you are absolutely fearless.

17:01.790 --> 17:04.330
Hey, they were running low
on white Zin.

17:04.330 --> 17:07.000
Somebody needed
to take action.

17:07.000 --> 17:08.460
I have a blast with you,

17:08.460 --> 17:10.250
and it's hard for me
to make female friends.

17:10.250 --> 17:11.540
I think
they're intimidated by me.

17:11.540 --> 17:12.750
[ Sighs ] So same.

17:12.750 --> 17:14.210
Mm.

17:14.210 --> 17:16.790
So, we're still going
to Cheyenne Pete's?

17:16.790 --> 17:18.120
Oh, hell yeah!

17:18.120 --> 17:20.170
We're drunk and fun. We're not
gonna waste that at home.

17:20.170 --> 17:21.460
No way!

17:21.460 --> 17:22.620
I'll be right back.

17:24.120 --> 17:26.080
I cut the order,
and she's my friend.

17:26.080 --> 17:28.330
In your face!

17:28.330 --> 17:30.170
That's great.
[ Chuckles ]

17:30.170 --> 17:31.210
I'm happy for you.

17:31.210 --> 17:32.830
We're going bull riding.

17:32.830 --> 17:34.710
Hey, I'm off in an hour.
Can I come?

17:34.710 --> 17:36.540
Becky, back off!

17:36.540 --> 17:39.290
It's like you reek
of desperation.

17:40.580 --> 17:43.170
♪♪

17:43.170 --> 17:45.080
You know, um,
I'm not complaining,

17:45.080 --> 17:46.580
but the smell
of those pain patches

17:46.580 --> 17:48.790
is a little overwhelming.

17:48.790 --> 17:50.460
Oh.

17:50.460 --> 17:52.540
I thought the mosquito candle
would cover it up.

17:52.540 --> 17:54.080
[ Chuckles ]
More wine?

17:54.080 --> 17:55.170
Sure.

18:01.000 --> 18:02.540
When I can venture
more than 10 feet

18:02.540 --> 18:03.790
from an outlet
next week,

18:03.790 --> 18:06.540
I'll take you
to a real restaurant.

18:06.540 --> 18:09.290
Um, since you brought up
next week,

18:09.290 --> 18:11.170
there's something
I want to talk to you about.

18:11.170 --> 18:12.710
Shoot.

18:12.710 --> 18:14.540
There's a promoter

18:14.540 --> 18:17.420
that offered my old band
a tour of the Midwest.

18:17.420 --> 18:19.670
That's great!

18:19.670 --> 18:20.830
How long?

18:20.830 --> 18:23.580
Three months,
at -- at least.

18:23.580 --> 18:25.420
Could be six.

18:25.420 --> 18:26.540
Wow.

18:26.540 --> 18:28.460
You know, the road
is a blast and all,

18:28.460 --> 18:31.500
but if you felt like
you...wanted me to stick around,

18:31.500 --> 18:33.120
I could pass on it.

18:33.120 --> 18:34.620
I wouldn't be comfortable

18:34.620 --> 18:37.250
costing you
that kind of an opportunity.

18:37.250 --> 18:38.830
I'd be okay with it.

18:38.830 --> 18:43.080
'Cause, you know, things are
going pretty well with us.

18:43.080 --> 18:45.210
I think they are, too.

18:46.920 --> 18:51.790
Dan, this may be my last chance
to go on the road.

18:51.790 --> 18:53.170
But I'll give that up.

18:54.380 --> 18:56.790
I think you need me.

18:56.790 --> 18:59.540
So if you want me
to stay...

18:59.540 --> 19:01.420
tell me to stay.

19:01.420 --> 19:03.420
Of course
I want you to stay.

19:04.380 --> 19:06.040
Okay.

19:06.040 --> 19:09.710
So, does that mean you're ready
for a real relationship,

19:09.710 --> 19:12.040
with everything
that goes with it?

19:17.670 --> 19:18.710
Got it.

19:20.500 --> 19:21.880
I got to go.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.420
[ Sighs ]

19:24.420 --> 19:26.080
Take care of yourself,
Dan Conner.

19:28.670 --> 19:30.580
That's what I do best.

19:33.040 --> 19:35.710
♪♪

19:35.710 --> 19:37.460
Hi.

19:37.460 --> 19:39.790
That's my granddaughter!
That's my granddaughter!

19:39.790 --> 19:41.540
First day! First day!

19:43.000 --> 19:44.420
Grandpa,
what are you doing here?

19:44.420 --> 19:46.620
Hopefully, embarrassing the hell
out of you.

19:46.620 --> 19:48.620
And letting you know
how proud I am of you.

19:48.620 --> 19:50.420
Thanks.

19:50.420 --> 19:53.120
And also probably gonna
pick up some tiger balm

19:53.120 --> 19:54.500
and a canned ham
while I'm here.

19:54.500 --> 19:55.710
Pbhhhht!

19:58.460 --> 20:00.330
Hey.

20:00.330 --> 20:03.000
Am I the only one in this family
who works?

20:03.000 --> 20:05.580
I just wanted
to say to you,

20:05.580 --> 20:08.380
in front of these vending
machines and this rocket ride,

20:08.380 --> 20:10.170
that I was wrong.

20:10.170 --> 20:12.580
I think what you're doing
is great.

20:12.580 --> 20:14.960
You found a way to go to
college. I mean, that's amazing.

20:14.960 --> 20:16.580
Really?

20:16.580 --> 20:19.120
I feel like
I'm...disappointing you.

20:19.120 --> 20:20.210
Never.

20:20.210 --> 20:22.120
I am so proud of you.

20:23.380 --> 20:25.210
You know,
I just want you to be happy.

20:25.210 --> 20:27.420
Well, you want to hear
something weird?

20:27.420 --> 20:28.920
I am happy.

20:28.920 --> 20:31.790
I'm gonna get a business degree,
and I'm gonna get rich

20:31.790 --> 20:32.920
exploiting
people like you.

20:32.920 --> 20:33.960
[ Chuckles ]

20:33.960 --> 20:36.580
Well,
that would be great.

20:36.580 --> 20:38.380
Can you do it quick enough
to send Mark to college?

20:38.380 --> 20:39.330
[ Chuckles ] Sure.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.330
Okay.

20:45.330 --> 20:47.460
It's my first day.
I got to get in there.

20:47.460 --> 20:48.290
Mm.

20:48.290 --> 20:49.580
Do you want me
to get fired?

20:49.580 --> 20:50.710
A little bit.

20:53.960 --> 20:56.080
Okay,
now that I'm painting,

20:56.080 --> 20:59.380
I finished something
that I'm really proud of,

20:59.380 --> 21:01.210
and I think that it would
look great in here --

21:01.210 --> 21:02.880
if you agree, partner.

21:02.880 --> 21:05.120
Of course you can
hang your painting in here.

21:05.120 --> 21:08.170
I call it "Dawn At Dusk."

21:12.790 --> 21:14.960
Wow.
You're really talented.

21:14.960 --> 21:17.380
If you put that up in here,
I quit.

21:17.380 --> 21:20.460
Okay, I will put it up
in the storage room.

21:20.460 --> 21:22.880
But when I finish
"Dawn At Dawn,"

21:22.880 --> 21:24.500
it's going up in here.
